data.text:
St Paul, MN, USA

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 44.949642, -93.093124.

St Paul is a large city and the capital of Minnesota state in the US. Together with Minneapolis, St. Paul form a large urban area, with the total population exceeding 3 million people, but of which only one tenth is living in St.Paul (about 300,000). The city is a beautiful settlement, situated on the banks of the Mississippi river, with modern central part and plenty of tourist attractions like the state Capitol, the Marjorie McNeely Conservatory, the historic James J. Hill House, and so on. St. Paul is a center of education, culture, sports, and commerce.
